      "label": "analyze_alternative_routes",
      "instructions": "Systematically evaluate the 8 potential mathematical routes/assumptions that could lead to an improvement of the exponent (e.g., different scaling arguments, improved pressure estimates, different regularity assumptions). For each route, provide a mathematical reason why it fails to yield a beta < 4/3."
    },
    {
      "label": "extremizer_construction",
      "instructions": "Construct or describe the mathematical object (e.g., a specific velocity field or pressure distribution) that acts as an extremizer, demonstrating that the exponent 4/3 cannot be improved because this object satisfies the Navier-Stokes equations (or a suitable approximation) while saturating the bound."
    },
    {
      "label": "conclusion_synthesis",
      "instructions": "Synthesize the findings to provide a binary answer (Yes/No) to whether the exponent can be improved, ensuring the conclusion is supported by the failure of the 8 routes and the existence of the extremizer."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent node will combine the results by first confirming the optimality of beta=4/3, then verifying that all 8 alternative mathematical paths are blocked, and finally validating the extremizer construction. The final answer must be a binary conclusion supported by these three pillars."
}
